##Hubei Central Rural anti-epidemic diary: Can Not buy masks, people returning from other places do not know the epidemic

Weixin Wangyiqingliu

Features introduction, through the fog, to find the truth. Netease Finance and economics under the original in-depth reporting team, focusing on the survey of listed companies.

By the second day of the Lunar New Year (January 26) , the village road to the outside was completely closed, only out. There were not many masks in the village, and they were not available in the town before the outbreak began. As of January 22, some of those returning from business trips did not even know about the outbreak.

Production | Netease Qingliu studio

By Liu Yadan, editor in chief | Yan Zhao

Tip Box:

stoolpigeon@service.netease.com

Coordinates in the central Hubei Province, a village, is located in central Hubei Province, Jingmen County intersection zone.

From 0 to 24 hours on 25 January 2020,17 new cases of COVID-19 infection were confirmed in Jingmen, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 38. As of 2400 hours on January 21,2020, two suspected cases of COVID-19 pneumonia had been found in our county (Shayang County) and one in neighboring county, Zhong Xiang, CCTV news reported.

Even in the age of the Internet, the source of information for many people in the countryside is the interpersonal communication between relatives, friends and neighbors.

My Aunt's family returned home on January 22(December 28) , had not heard of the epidemic at all, and some people in the village were only informed by phone halfway home. My cousin, who did not know about the epidemic, picked up a relative who was returning home from Wuhan in his car, without a mask or protection. On January 25, (the first day of the first lunar month) , the city was also closed, my cousin just realized the seriousness, he was very flustered, in the wechat family group asked us how to do.

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, the village road was closed

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
(on the second day of the Lunar New Year, the village stopped all New Year activities, villagers stood on the road chatting. Wearing masks are still not many. Photo by Liu Yadan)

At first it was US young people coming home from out of town. At first, we tried to persuade our families to wear masks and stay indoors. In the family group, my sister and I kept up to date. On January 21, I got up in the morning and found that my father did not wear a mask to the market to sell Lotus root, was very nervous and angry. Back then, the Internet was full of stories about "the generation of parents who don't wear masks. ". My Dad said he saw, like, one in ten people wearing masks at the town fair. The town also can not buy medical masks, my father bought a few labor insurance masks home, gave one to my aunt.

On January 22, we had suspected cases in Shayang, the county seat, and Zhongxiang, the city of Lin County, Shanxi. But very few people in the village wear masks. Even though my sister and I kept texting in the family group, cousins were looking for a room downtown to play Mah Jongg. I wore a white face mask that my father had bought and walked from the end of the village to the end of the village several times during a group walk at night, which I considered to be epidemic propaganda and popularization. This Day, the door of our village's commissary, also posted a notice of epidemic situation.

(notice of the epidemic has been put up in the village. Photo by Liu Yadan)

Considering that the medical system in the county and urban areas is much weaker than that in Wuhan, and that people in the countryside generally do not take it seriously and are not prepared for it, I keep telling my parents not to contact outsiders. When my aunt came home from a trip, I half jokingly refused to make contact with them. On the one hand, I came back from Wuhan without a 14-day "incubation period" ; on the other hand, they did not realize the defensive measures, casual contact with the crowd.

On January 23rd, the city of Wuhan was closed. I began to persuade my father, New Year not to call, do not let relatives and friends to call at home, successfully persuaded my father, then began to go to the family group initiative do not call New Year. That night, our village cadres wearing masks to our home registration of migrants, this time is the whole village began to attach importance to. I said to the village cadres: "Give us a mask. " The village cadres said: "I do not have a mask, how to give you. "

On the morning of January 24(December 30) , village cadres were driving cars and using loudspeakers to spread news of the epidemic in the village. I cooperate with parents, call friends and relatives, "this year serious epidemic, not new year... ". We all understand each other, the village in the New Year this few days to get married, birthday celebrations are basically cancelled.

On January 25(the first day of the first lunar month) , our city has been closed, the city's First People's Hospital has also issued a request for medical supplies, the village car or regular morning and evening publicity. It was raining and the temperature was very low. When I got up in the morning, no one went out in the village.

On the first day of the New Year, all the villagers pay New Year greetings to each other. This year, everyone stays at home and stays indoors. After 2:00 pm, my parents saw boring TV, covered with blankets to sleep until 5:00 pm. In the evening, we were told that the road in the village would be closed and only one way in and one way out. At this time my mother to my aunt and uncle continue to call, explain the second day of the first month back to my grandmother's New Year are also cancelled. On the phone, we heard aunts from neighboring towns still visiting relatives, gathering to play cards. It's just the next town over. I don't know what's going on with them.

January 26(the second day of the Lunar New Year) , the rain stopped, the village people yesterday all stayed at home bored, began two or three gathered at the village mouth chat. That day the village road to the outside has been closed, there is a suspected case of new-type pneumonia. Some of the people who come out to chat in the village also wear masks, most of them are not wearing masks. "Boring" has become the biggest emotion among friends and relatives on Wechat. At the same time, I find my family is running out of fruit and there are enough vegetables in the field. Before the outbreak, our family temporarily purchased rice and gas.

(village officials post road closures in the village. Photo by Liu Yadan)

(village closure notice, access only, the junction between the village and the neighbouring village is closed. Photo by Liu Yadan)

Village Outbreak Watch schedule:

On January 21, a suspected case was discovered in Jingmen. Dad did not wear a mask to go out to the market to sell Lotus root, I am worried. Dad came back to say that less than a tenth of the town wore masks, medical masks and N95 masks are not available.

On January 22, there were suspected cases in the county. The aunts are back home. They don't know the epidemic yet. That night the village put up the first epidemic notice.

January 23rd. Village officials began to register the migrants in the village. I said to the village cadres: "Give us a mask. " The village cadres said: "I do not have a mask, how to give you. "

24 January. The village began to broadcast the news van sooner or later.

25 January. On the first day of the first lunar month, no one in the village came to pay New Year's greetings. Phone learned that the sister-in-law in the town is also home to play cards.

26 January. The village is closed and all roads leading to the neighbouring village are closed except for access. Some of the people who come out to chat in the village also wear masks, most of them are not wearing masks.

Liu Yadan is a senior writer at Qingliu Studio, based in Guangzhou.
